				h2 Import list from CSV
				button.button.minor.m-1-1.toggle-collapse âž• Expand
			.tool.collapsed
				p.lh-1p5.
					Paste a CSV in below and click import to import a list.
				p: strong Please note:
				ul.lh-1p5
					li If the subscriber (identified by their email address) already exists in the database, they will skipped.
					li If the subscriber appears multiple times in the import data, only the first one instance will be used.
					li <b>For a much faster import</b>, the above checks can be disabled using the 'Skip duplicate check' checkbox below. <strong>Please ensure there are no duplicates</strong> when doing this; otherwise duplicated subscribers will receive emails multiple times.
					li To include tags for subscribers, include a list of tags separated by commas in a field escaped by quotation marks; e.g.: "email@example.com","tags,tagb"
					li <b>Subscribers must have at least one list tag to be able to send to them</b>. This basically means one tag starting with <q>list-</q>. To automatically add subscribers to lists, include the respective list tag or tags in the tags column; e.g.: "list-main,list-subgroup". Then, ensure you have a list with a list id that is the same as the tag in your <a href="/lists/index.html">lists</a>.
				p
					label
						input#import-skip-duplicate-check(type="checkbox")
						span Skip duplicate check
				div.m-b-1
					textarea#import-data.input.w-100(
						style='min-height:50vh'
						placeholder="email,firstName,tags\n\"test@example.com\",\"Robin\",\"tag-a,tab-b\""
